-- Ruble Gains Fourth Day to Dollar as Crude Climbs; Bonds Advance
-- B y   D e n i s   M a t e r n o v s k y
-- 2012-03-16T16:16:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-16/ruble-declines-versus-dollar-steady-against-currency-basket.html
The ruble strengthened for a fourth
day against the dollar as crude oil, the country’s main export
earner, climbed.  The Russian currency increased 0.3 percent to 29.2816 per
dollar at the close in Moscow, taking its five-day gain to 0.8
percent. The ruble depreciated 0.5 percent to 38.5727 against
the euro, leaving it 0.1 weaker percent versus the central
bank’s euro-dollar basket at 33.4626. The country’s sovereign
dollar bonds maturing in 2020 rose, lowering the yield four
basis points to 3.911 percent.  Crude for April delivery rose 66 cents, or 0.6 percent, to
$105.77 a barrel on the  New York Mercantile Exchange . Oil and
natural gas account for about 50 percent of  Russia ’s state
revenue.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Denis Maternovsky in Moscow at 
 dmaternovsky@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
